  "prompt": "What are 13.1 and 26.2 stickers and what do they mean?",
  "response": "13.1 and 26.2 stickers are commonly seen on vehicles and typically indicate the owner's accomplishment in long-distance running events. Specifically:\n\n- **13.1** refers to a half marathon, which is 13.1 miles long (approximately 21.1 kilometers).\n- **26.2** refers to a full marathon, which is 26.2 miles long (approximately 42.2 kilometers).\n\nThese stickers are a way for runners to proudly showcase their achievements and dedication to the sport.",
